This paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category (cs.CL) because it deals with multilingual speech recognition, which is a common NLP problem. It could also belong to the Sound (cs.SD) sub-category because it deals with acoustic models. Additionally, it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category because it proposes a new approach using neural networks. The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories are also possible because the paper deals with adaptive approaches and modulating networks.
